<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-08"><hi rend="italic">August 8,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports delay to signing of the final protocol caused by
                        objections raised by British Government against the international commission
                        for the revision of tariff, which was unanimously accepted June 11, and the
                        Chinese Government so informed; also by wanting to insert in the protocol a
                        clause highly objectionable to several of the powers.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>